headline.print_headline: Central African Republic Says Violence Plotted to Provoke Coup
headline.main: Central African Republic Says Violence Plotted to Provoke Coup

lead_paragraph: Central African Republic's transitional government on Tuesday said that several days of violence last week, the most serious in months in which about a dozen people were killed, was part of a purported plot to overthrow the administration.
